						<summary>

						<p>On the <hi rend="italic">gōmukha</hi> (water chute) in the south side of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Mantrapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>The record may palaeographically be assigned to 13th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It registers the gift, probably of the water chute, where the record is engraved, by a certain Tirukkāppunīr-aḻagiyāṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vīraśiṅgarāyaṉ of Ilattaippuliyūr, who use to offer food to the deity Tiruvuśāttāṉam-uḍaiyār.</p>						

						</summary>
